aa(lp32
VThat's called a babygram,
p33
aVa full X-ray of a child's body, a little infant's body.
p34
aVAs you look on the top side of this,
p35
aVthat's where the heart and lungs are supposed to be.
p36
aVAs you look at the bottom end, that's where the abdomen is,
p37
aVand that's where the intestines are supposed to be.
p38
aVAnd you can see how there's sort of that translucent area
p39
aVthat made its way up into the right side of this child's chest.
p40
aVAnd those are the intestines \u2014 in the wrong place.
p41
aVAs a result, they're pushing on the lungs
p42
aVand making it very difficult for this poor baby to breathe.
