aa(lp150
VSo, a quick study in neurosurgery.
p151
aVThere's the brain,
p152
aVand you can see the cranium surrounding the brain.
p153
aVWhat surrounds the brain, between the brain and cranium,
p154
aVis something called cerebrospinal fluid or fluid,
p155
aVwhich acts as a shock absorber.
p156
aVIn your heads right now,
p157
aVthere is cerebrospinal fluid just bathing your brains
p158
aVand making its way around.
p159
aVIt's produced in one area and flows through,
p160
aVand then is re-exchanged.
p161
aVAnd this beautiful flow pattern occurs for all of us.
p162
aVBut unfortunately in some children,
p163
aVthere's a blockage of this flow pattern,
p164
aVmuch like a traffic jam.
p165
aVAs a result, the fluid accumulates,
p166
aVand the brain is pushed aside.
p167
aVIt has difficulty growing.
p168
aVAs a result, the child loses neurologic milestones.
p169
aVThis is a devastating disease in children.
