aa(lp171
VThe cure for this is surgery.
p172
aVThe traditional surgery is to take a bit of the cranium off,
p173
aVa bit of the skull,
p174
aVdrain this fluid out, stick a drain in place,
p175
aVand then eventually bring this drain internal to the body.
p176
aVBig operation.
p177
aVBut some great news is that advances in neurosurgical care
p178
aVhave allowed us to develop minimally invasive approaches
p179
aVto this surgery.
p180
aVThrough a small pinhole, a camera can be inserted,
p181
aVled into the deep brain structure,
p182
aVand cause a little hole in a membrane that allows all that fluid to drain,
p183
aVmuch like it would in a sink.
p184
aVAll of a sudden, the brain is no longer under pressure,
p185
aVcan re-expand
p186
aVand we cure the child through a single-hole incision.
